ay]]\n| WrittenBy       = [[Michael Hitchcock]]\n| DirectedBy      = Brad Falchuk\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|2012|11|8}}\n| ProdCode        = 4ARC05\n| Viewers         = 5.68<ref name=\"glee4x05\">{{cite web|url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2012/11/09/thursday-final-ratingsthe-big-bang-theory-vampire-diaries-greys-anatomy-adjusted-up-the-office-parks-rec-scandal-rock-center-adjusted-down/156810/ |title=Thursday Final Ratings:'The Big Bang Theory', 'Vampire Diaries' & 'Grey's Anatomy' Adjusted Up, 'The Office', 'Parks & Rec', 'Scandal' & 'Rock Center' Adjusted Down |work=TV by the Numbers|last=Kondolojy|first=Amanda|date=November 9, 2012|accessdate=November 9, 2012}}</ref>\n| ShortSummary    = The McKinley High production of ''[[Grease (musical)|Grease]]'' is being cast, and after [[Artie Abrams|Artie]] recruits Finn to help him direct, he calls in McKinley graduates [[Mercedes Jones|Mercedes]] and [[Mike Chang|Mike]] to help him and Finn with auditions for the musical. Competitors for the lead role of Danny include Jake and football player Ryder Lynn ([[Blake Jenner]]), while Marley and Kitty are rivals for Sandy, the female lead. Will also makes a big decision.\n| LineColor       = 56C8BA\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|Glee (season 4)\n| EpisodeNumber   = 72\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 6\n| Title           = [[Glease]]\n| WrittenBy       = [[Roberto Aguirre-Sacasa]]\n| DirectedBy      = [[Michael Uppendahl]]\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|2012|11|15}}\n| ProdCode        = 4ARC06\n| Viewers         = 5.22<ref name=\"glee4x06\">{{cite web|url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2012/11/16/thursday-final-ratings-the-big-bang-theory-vampire-diaries-greys-anatomy-last-resort-scandal-adjusted-down/158003/ |title=Thursday Final Ratings: 'The Big Bang Theory', 'Vampire Diaries', 'Grey's Anatomy' & 'The Office' Adjusted Up; 'Last Resort & 'Scandal' Adjusted Down |work=TV by the Numbers|last=Bibel|first=Sara|date=November 16, 2012|accessdate=November 16, 2012}}</ref>\n| Sho