inley to help the New Directions prepare for Regionals, along with Mike and Mercedes. Artie is keeping a secret from his mom (special guest star [[Katey Sagal]]), but Kitty steps in to help Artie come clean. Rachel worries when Cassandra finds out about her ''Funny Girl'' audition, but is surprised when Cassandra changes her attitude towards her.\n| LineColor       = 56C8BA\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|Glee (season 4)\n| EpisodeNumber   = 88\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 22\n| Title           = [[All or Nothing (Glee)|All or Nothing]]\n| WrittenBy       = Ian Brennan\n| DirectedBy      = Bradley Buecker\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|2013|5|9}}\n| ProdCode        = 4ARC22\n| Viewers         = 5.92<ref name=\"glee4x22\">{{cite web|title=Thursday Final Ratings: 'Big Bang Theory', 'Grey's Anatomy', 'American Idol', 'Vampire Diaries', 'Two and a Half Men', 'Wipeout', & 'Elementary' Adjusted Up; 'Glee' Adjusted Down|url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2013/05/10/thursday-final-ratings-big-bang-theory-greys-anatomy-american-idol-vampire-diaries-two-and-a-half-men-wipeout-glee-adjusted-down/181920/|work=TV by the Numbers|last=Kondolojy|first=Amanda|date=May 10, 2013|accessdate=May 10, 2013}}</ref>\n| ShortSummary    = Rachel has her ''Funny Girl'' callback whilst the New Directions take on the Hoosierdaddies with lead singer Frida Romero ([[Jessica Sanchez]]) and the Waffletoots (Yale Whiffenpoofs, with lead singer Brandon Levin) at Regionals. Brittany returns from MIT to McKinley with a new attitude. Ryder finally discovers who Katie is. Will and Emma decide to marry in surprise in the show choir room while Blaine plans on proposing to Kurt.\n| LineColor       = 56C8BA\n}}\n}}</onlyinclude>\n\n==Production==\n\n===Development===\nThe fourth season will continue to be set at McKinley High in Ohio and follow several of the just-graduated characters to New York, and will be set at a performing arts school (NYADA) there. The Ohio portion of the show will feature a number of new characters.<ref name=\"HR514\"/>\n\nCo-creator [[Ryan Murphy (writer)|Ryan Murphy]] has confirmed that all regular cast members from the third season will be returning to the show for its fourth season, though \"it doesn't mean everyone will be doing 22 episodes\".<ref name=\"VultureMurphy\">{{cite web|url=http://www.vulture.com/2012/05/ryan-murphy-tells-us-whos-staying-on-glee.html |title=Exclusive: Ryan Murphy Tells Us Who\u2019s Staying on ''Glee'' |first=Denise |last=Martin |work=[[Vulture.com]] |date=May 17, 2012|accessdate=May 18, 2012}}</ref>\n\nFox announced on May 14, 2012, that ''Glee'' would be moving to Thursday nights at 9&nbsp;pm ET for the fourth season. Episodes aired after that evening's 8&nbsp;pm ET music competition \"results\" shows\u2014''[[The X Factor (U.S.)|The X Factor]]'' in the fall and ''[[American Idol]]'' in midseason.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tvline.com/2012/05/14/fox-fall-tv-lineup-2012/ |title=Fox Fall Schedule Revealed: ''Glee'' Shifts to Thursday, ''Touch'' Moves to Friday and More! |last=Ausiello|first=Michael|authorlink=Michael Ausiello|work=[[TVLine]]|publisher=[[PMC (company)|PMC]]|date=May 14, 2012|accessdate=May 15, 2012}}</ref> The season premiered on September 13, 2012<ref name=\"FoxFall12\">{{cite web|url=http://www.foxflash.com/div.php/main/page?aID=1z2z1z25z1z8&ID=8721|title=FOX announces fall premiere dates for the 2012\u20132013 season|work=Fox Flash|date=June 18, 2012|accessdate=June 18, 2012|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120621165324/http://www.foxflash.com/div.php/main/page?aID=1z2z1z25z1z8&ID=8721|archivedate=June 21, 2012}}</ref> with the second episode of the season serving as the show's second [[Britney Spears]] tribute, featuring eight of her songs.<ref name=\"EW515\">{{cite web|url=http://insidetv.ew.com/2012/05/15/glee-scoop-second-britney-tribute-exclusive/|title={{-'}}Glee' scoop: New Britney Spears tribute planned for fall; plus details on Kate Hudson's role \u2013 Exclusive|first=Tim|last=Stack|work=Inside TV|publisher=Entertainment Weekly|date=May 15, 2012|accessdate=May 15, 2012}}</ref>\n\nIn the UK, ''Glee'' airs as part of [[Sky 1|Sky 1 Sundays]] at 8pm and broadcast began on January 6, 2013.<ref name=\"Glee in the UK\">{{cite web|title=2013 kicks off in GLEE-ful mode|url=http://sky1.sky.com/glee/sky1-kicks-off-2013-in-gleeful-mode|publisher=BskyB|accessdate=11 February 2013}}</ref>\n\nSome changes were made to the show's writing staff. Marti Noxon announced that she would no longer be a writer or consulting producer on the show,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/martinoxon/status/209761014244311041|title=I will not be on Glee 4. Love the show and will miss all the good peeps. So all ya'll Gleeks can unfollow and stop yelling at me!|first=Marti|last=Noxon|work=Twitter|date=June 4, 2012|accessdate=June 4, 2012}}</ref> and co-executive producer and writer [[Ali Adler]] stated that she would be scaling back her work on ''Glee'' to focus on her new [[NBC]] comedy ''[[The New Normal (TV series)|The New Normal]]'', which she co-created with Murphy.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.afterellen.com/content/2012/07/ali-adler-new-normal-and-stepping-back-glee|title=Ali Adler on ''The New Normal'' and stepping back from ''Glee''|first=Trish|last=Bendix|work=[[After Ellen]]|date=July 26, 2012|accessdate=August 11, 2012|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120729045745/http://www.afterellen.com/content/2012/07/ali-adler-new-normal-and-stepping-back-glee|archivedate=July 29, 2012}}</ref>\n\nOn July 14, 2012, Glee attended the [[San Diego Comic-Con]] in California. Co-creator [[Brad Falchuk]] revealed that [[Damian McGinty]] (Rory) would not be returning in the fall but stated he could return in the spring. Falchuk announced that [[Vanessa Lengies]] (Sugar) and [[Samuel Larsen]] (Joe) would be returning. Falchuk also had aspirations to bring back [[Alex Newell]] (Wade) at some point during season four. Other season details include the following: Sue had her baby when season four commenced; episodes alternated between Ohio and New York, much like McKinley High and Dalton Academy in Season 2; and Kurt ([[Chris Colfer]]) remained in Ohio before moving to New York. [[Brad Falchuk]] also revealed that Will ([[Matthew Morrison]]) and Emma ([[Jayma Mays]]) would still be engaged when the season began, and he went on to state there would be many new faces during the season, also commenting that Rachel would have a roommate and new friends in New York. Season four featured a teaming up of Coach Roz ([[NeNe Leakes]]) and Sue ([[Jane Lynch]]) to take down Principal Figgins ([[Iqbal Theba]]).<ref name=\"HR714\">{{cite web |url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/comic-con-2012-glee-season-4-349280 |title=Comic-Con 2012: 'Glee': Damian McGinty Not Returning, Sue Gives Birth and 13 Season 4 Spoilers |work=The Hollywood Reporter |first=Lesley |last=Goldberg |date=July 14, 2012 |accessdate=August 1, 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=9jA9RcEE5qI |title=Glee Comic-con panel \u2013 SDCC 2012 1/3 |publisher=YouTube |date=July 14, 2012 |accessdate=August 1, 2012}}</ref>\n\nOn July 31, 2012, executive producer Murphy revealed on his Twitter account that the first group number of the season would be a cover of [[Adele]]'s \"[[Chasing Pavements]]\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/MrRPMurphy/status/230371265561624578 |title=@massivegleek The first group number is \"Chasing Pavements\" by the fabulous Miss @OfficialAdele. |first=Ryan|last=Murphy|publisher=[[Twitter]]|date=July 31, 2012|accessdate=July 31, 2012}}</ref> Murphy also tweeted that there would be an episode titled \"The Break-Up\" and a two-part Thanksgiving episode in which the Sectionals competition will take place.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/MrRPMurphy/status/230361953997049856 |title=@ClaireMilne The writers are working on an episode called \"The Break-Up\" that I'm really excited about. |first=Ryan|last=Murphy|publisher=[[Twitter]]|date=July 31, 2012|accessdate=July 31, 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/MrRPMurphy/status/230361141405184001 |title=@ftlquamduck Yes! Planning a great two-part Thanksgiving episode. Sectionals happens during Turkey Time this year! |first=Ryan|last=Murphy|publisher=[[Twitter]]|date=July 31, 2012|accessdate=July 31, 2012}}</ref> Murphy also stated that the show would be doing another Christmas episode this season.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/MrRPMurphy/status/253310344112504832|title=@shanoreily I actually am doing Christmas episodes on all three shows.|first=Ryan|last=Murphy|work=[[Twitter]]|date=October 2, 2012|accessdate=October 5, 2012}}</ref>\n\nExecutive producer Falchuk stated that season four will not revolve around relationships as much as past seasons, commenting, \"Relationships in general will be less of a focus this year, I personally think a lot of these characters are more interesting not in relationships. And I think with a lot of them we will be exploring that. Whether they break up or not, we\u2019re really focused on giving them more individual stories.\"<ref name=ep4>{{cite web|url=http://tvline.com/2012/08/16/glee-season-4-episode-4-the-breakup-spoilers/|title=Exclusive: Glee Exec on Season 4's Big 'Breakup' Episode: 'It's Like Titanic \u2013 Not All Will Make It{{'-}}|first=Michael|last=Ausiello|work=[[TVLine]]|publisher=[[PMC (company)|PMC]]|date=August 16, 2012|accessdate=August 16, 2012}}</ref>\n\n===Filming===\nSeason four of Glee began filming on Tuesday, July 24, 2012.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.eonline.com/news/331574/lea-michele-ok-with-glee-s-emmy-snubs-quot-i-m-very-proud-of-our-last-season-quot |title=Lea Michele OK With Glee's Emmy Snubs: \"I'm Very Proud of Our Last Season{{\"-}} |first=Marc |last=Malkin |work=[[E! Online]] |publisher=[[NBCUniversal]] |date=July 19, 2012 |accessdate=August 1, 2012}}</ref> A substantial amount of exterior shots depicting New York City were shot on location in that city.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.digitalspy.com/tv/news/a398892/glee-season-4-on-location-in-new-york-city-pictures.html|title={{-'}}Glee' Season 4 on location in New York City: Pictures|first=Donna|last=Cini|work=[[Digital Spy]]|date=August 12, 2012|accessdate=August 16, 2012}}</ref> Studio recording for the season began earlier, by July 19, 2012, with [[Jenna Ushkowitz]] and [[Heather Morris]] recording on that day.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/JennaUshkowitz/status/225992455621857281 |title=JennaUshkowitz: Back in the recording studio |first=Jenna |last=Ushkowitz |publisher=[[Twitter]] |date=July 19, 2012 |accessdate=August 1, 2012}}</ref>\n\n==Cast==\nFox credits fourteen main cast members for the season: [[Matthew Morrison]] as glee club director Will Schuester; [[Jane Lynch]] as cheerleading coach Sue Sylvester; [[Chris Colfer]], [[Lea Michele]], [[Cory Monteith]], [[Amber Riley]], [[Naya Rivera]], [[Mark Salling]] and [[Harry Shum, Jr.]] as McKinley graduates and former glee club members Kurt Hummel, Rachel Berry, Finn Hudson, Mercedes Jones, Santana Lopez, Noah \"Puck\" Puckerman and Mike Chang respectively; and [[Darren Criss]], [[Kevin McHale (actor)|Kevin McHale]], [[Heather Morris]], [[Chord Overstreet]] and [[Jenna Ushkowitz]] as current glee club members Blaine Anderson, Artie Abrams, Brittany Pierce, Sam Evans, and Tina Cohen-Chang respectively.<ref name=\"New Rachel\">{{cite episode |title=The New Rachel|episodelink=The New Rachel|series=Glee |serieslink=Glee (TV series) |credits=[[Brad Falchuk]] (director), [[Ryan Murphy (writer)|Ryan Murphy]] (writer)|network=[[Fox Broadcasting Company|Fox]] |airdate=September 13, 2012 |season=4 |number=1}}</ref> Overstreet received a contractual upgrade, having formerly been a recurring cast member.<ref name=\"HR723\">{{cite web|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/glee-chord-overstreet-returning-season-4-353225 |title={{-'}}Glee': Chord Overstreet Officially Returning as Series Regular |first=Lesley|last=Goldberg|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|date=July 23, 2012|accessdate=July 24, 2012}}</ref> Two previous main cast member who are no longer series regulars are [[Jayma Mays]] as guidance counselor Emma Pillsbury, and [[Dianna Agron]] as [[Quinn Fabray]], though both are listed among the guest cast for this season.<ref name=\"Thanksgiving\">{{cite episode |title=Thanksgiving|episodelink=Thanksgiving (Glee)|series=Glee |serieslink=Glee (TV series) |credits=Bradley Buecker (director), [[Russel Friend]] & [[Garrett Lerner]] (writers)|network=[[Fox Broadcasting Company|Fox]] |airdate=November 29, 2012 |season=4 |number=8}}</ref>\n\nTwo actresses appeared in multi-episode guest-starring arcs as part of the New York sequences: [[Sarah Jessica Parker]] as Isabelle Wright (first reported as Isabelle Klempt),<ref name=\"HR514\">{{cite web|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/glee-sarah-jessica-parker-kate-hudson-season-4-323938 |title={{-'}}Glee': Sarah Jessica Parker, Kate Hudson Set for Show-Within-a-Show Season 4 |first=Lesley|last=Goldberg|work=The Hollywood Reporter|date=May 14, 2012|accessdate=May 15, 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.vogue.com/vogue-daily/article/exclusive-video-sarah-jessica-parker-and-vogue-com-on-glee/#1|title=Exclusive Video: Sarah Jessica Parker and Vogue.com on ''Glee''|work=Vogue.com|date=September 25, 2012|accessdate=September 25, 2012|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120927015649/http://www.vogue.com/vogue-daily/article/exclusive-video-sarah-jessica-parker-and-vogue-com-on-glee/#1|archivedate=September 27, 2012}}</ref> and [[Kate Hudson]] as Cassandra July.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.accesshollywood.com/glee-scoop-sarah-jessica-parkers-vogue-connection-and-kate-hudsons-character-name_article_67216 |title=Glee Scoop! Sarah Jessica Parker's Vogue Connection & Kate Hudson's Character Name |first=Jolie |last=Lash |work=[[Access Hollywood]] |publisher=[[NBCUniversal]] |date=July 16, 2012 |accessdate=August 20, 2012}}</ref> Parker's character is a mentor to Kurt, and Hudson's character is Rachel's dance teacher at NYADA;<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tvguide.com/News/Glee-Season4-Secrets-1049172.aspx|title=Keck's Exclusives: New ''Glee'' Season Secrets!|first=William|last=Keck|work=TV Guide|date=June 24, 2012|accessdate=June 25, 2012}}</ref> Hudson was originally reported to be appearing in six episodes during the fall.<ref name=\"HR514\"/><ref name=\"EW515\"/>\n\nSeveral new recurring characters were added for the new season. [[Dean Geyer]] as Brody Weston, a handsome junior at Rachel's new school, [[Jacob Artist]] as McKinley sophomore Jake Puckerman, [[Puck (Glee)|Puck]]'s ([[Mark Salling]]) younger half brother, [[Becca Tobin]] as Kitty, a cheerleader, and [[Melissa Benoist]] as Marley Rose.<ref name=\"TVL20120731\">{{Cite news|url=http://tvline.com/2012/07/31/glee-becca-tobin-melissa-benoist/|title=''Glee'' Exclusive: Meet the New Girls! |accessdate=July 31, 2012|date=July 31, 2012|work=[[TVLine]]|publisher=[[PMC (company)|PMC]] | first=Michael | last=Ausiello}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://tvline.com/2012/08/29/glee-season-4-videos-rachel-cassandra-brody/ |title=''Glee'' Video Sneak Peeks: Rachel Gets Dissed and Meets the New (Nude!) Guy in Her Life |first=Kimberly |last=Roots |work=[[TVLine]]|date=August 29, 2012|accessdate=August 30, 2012}}</ref><ref name=\"GeyerArtist\">{{Cite news|url=http://tvline.com/2012/07/23/glee-season-4-cast/|title=Glee Scoop: Meet the 'Freshman' Class (Including Love Interest For Rachel, Puck's Younger Bro)|accessdate=July 23, 2012|date=July 23, 2012|work=[[TVLine]] |publisher=[[PMC (company)|PMC]] | first=Michael |last=Ausiello}}</ref> Marley's mother Millie was played by [[Trisha Rae Stahl]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/glee-season-4-spoilers-melissa-benoist-marley-mom-370364 |title={{-'}}Glee': Marley's Mother to Recur in Season 4 |first=Lesley|last=Goldberg|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|date=September 14, 2012|accessdate=September 14, 2012}}</ref>\n\n''[[The Glee Project]]'' winner [[Blake Jenner]] was given a recurring role\u2014set for at least seven episodes\u2014starting with the fifth episode; he plays Ryder Lynn, a new McKinley student, who joins New Directions with Finn's aid.<ref name=\"TVL20120828\">{{Cite news|url=http://tvline.com/2012/08/28/walking-dead-season-3-death-spoiler/ |title=Ask Ausiello: Spoilers on ''Walking Dead'', ''Once'', ''Castle'', ''Gossip Girl'', ''New Girl'', ''SOA'' and More! |accessdate=August 28, 2012|date=August 28, 2012|work=[[TVLine]]|publisher=[[PMC (company)|PMC]] | first=Michael | last=Ausiello}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://tvline.com/2012/09/26/glee-finn-returns-season-4-episode-4/|title=''Glee'' Exclusive: Cory Monteith on Finn's Return, 'Break-Up' Drama and Being Called a [Spoiler]|first=Michael|last=Ausiello|work=[[TVLine]]|publisher=[[PMC (company)|PMC]] |date=September 26, 2012|accessdate=September 26, 2012}}</ref> Jenner has commented that he would enjoy playing a character like Finn.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/glee-project-winner-blake-jenner-glee-season-4-362655|title={{-'}}The Glee Project' Winner Blake Jenner: 'I'd Love to Be a Finn-Type Character{{'-}}|first=Lesley|last=Goldberg|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|date=August 15, 2012|accessdate=August 15, 2012}}</ref> ''Glee Project'' runner-up [[Ali Stroker]] had a guest role on \"I Do\" as Betty, [[Emma Pillsbury|Emma's]] niece and Artie's love interest.<ref>{{cite web|title=Behind the Scenes of Ali Stroker\u2019s Glee Debut \u2014 Exclusive|url=http://www.wetpaint.com/glee/articles/behind-the-scenes-of-ali-strokers-glee-debut-exclusive|publisher=Wetpaint}}</ref>\n\nActress [[Whoopi Goldberg]] reprised her season three role, Carmen Tibideaux. She recurred throughout the season.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/glee-whoopi-goldberg-season-4-samuel-larsen-alex-newell-returning-361453|title=''Glee'' Brings Back Whoopi Goldberg for Season 4 (Exclusive)|first=Lesley|last=Goldberg|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|date=August 17, 2012|accessdate=August 17, 2012}}</ref> Other recurring guests who returned include [[Vanessa Lengies]] as [[Sugar Motta]], [[Samuel Larsen]] as [[Joe Hart (Glee)|Joe Hart]] and [[Alex Newell]] as [[Wade Adams|Wade \"Unique\" Adams]].<ref name=\"GeyerArtist\" /><ref name=\"TVL20120724\">{{Cite news|url=http://tvline.com/2012/07/24/glee-vanessa-lengies-sugar-season-4/|title=Exclusive: ''Glee'' Adds More Sugar in Season 4 |accessdate=July 31, 2012|date=July 31, 2012|work=[[TVLine]]|publisher=[[PMC (company)|PMC]] | first=Michael | last=Ausiello}}</ref> [[Lauren Potter]] as cheerleader [[Becky Jackson]] also returned, and filmed scenes on August 22, 2012.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/TheLaurenPotter/status/238471878807785474 |title=TheLaurenPotter: So tired after a long day at McKinley High. But I can't wait to go back again. I hope this proves I'm the real Lauren! |first=Lauren |last=Potter |publisher=[[Twitter]]|date=August 22, 2012|accessdate=August 31, 2012}}</ref> [[Damian McGinty]] ([[Rory Flanagan]]) was not a part of the regular cast, but he made a special appearance in \"[[Glee, Actually]]\" as Artie's guardian angel in a dream sequence. From the cast of recurring adult characters, [[Dot Jones|Dot-Marie Jones]] as [[Shannon Beiste|Coach Beiste]],<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://tvline.com/2012/07/19/glee-dot-marie-jones-emmy-season-4/ |title=Glee's Dot-Marie Jones Talks Emmy Nod, Season 4 Status, Loving/Hating Her Pivotal Episode |date=July 19, 2012|accessdate=July 24, 2012|work=[[TVLine]]|publisher=[[PMC (company)|PMC]] | first=Michael | last=Slezak}}</ref> [[Iqbal Theba]] as [[Principal Figgins]] and [[NeNe Leakes]] as Coach [[Roz Washington]] all returned.<ref name=\"HR714\"/> [[Jessalyn Gilsig]], like McGinty, made a special appearance in \"[[Glee, Actually]]\" in Artie's dream sequence, reprising her role as [[Terri Schuester]]. [[Grant Gustin]] returned as Dalton Academy Warbler [[Sebastian Smythe]], and the group's new leader, Hunter, was played by [[Nolan Gerard Funk]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/glee-season-4-spoilers-warblers-nolan-gerard-funk-375338/|title={{-'}}Glee' Adds Canadian Actor-Singer as New Lead Warbler|first=Lesley|last=Goldberg|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|date=October 1, 2012|accessdate=October 1, 2012}}</ref> [[Ashley Fink]] also returned for a guest appearance in \"Sadie Hawkins\" reprising her role as [[Lauren Zizes]] after being absent for most of Season 3 and the first ten episodes of Season 4.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tvline.com/2012/12/20/ashley-fink-glee-season-4-lauren-zizes/|title={{-'}}Glee Scoop: Ashley Fink Books Return|first=Michael|last=Slezak|work=[[TV Line]]|date=December 20, 2012|accessdate=December 20, 2012}}</ref> [[American Idol]] season 11 runner-up [[Jessica Sanchez]] appeared near the end of the season as a student from a rival school named Frida Romero, who has been described as a \"powerhouse singer\".<ref>{{cite web|title=Jessica Sanchez's ''Glee'' Role Revealed: She'll Be A 'Legendary Diva{{'-}} |url=http://hollywoodlife.com/2013/03/25/glee-jessica-sanchez-role-diva-finn/|work=March 25, 2013|publisher=Hollywoodlife|accessdate=April 7, 2013}}</ref>\n[[Idina Menzel]] also reprised her role as [[Shelby Corcoran]] for a guest appearance in \"Sweet Dreams\" for the first time since her multi-episode arc in season 3.\n\n==Reception==\n\n===Critical response===\nThe [[review aggregator]] website [[Rotten Tomatoes]] gives the season a 65% with an average rating of 7.07/10, based on 23 reviews. The site's critics consensus reads, \"''Glee'' may have lost a few of its major characters, but several strong storylines help to compensate, and the songs are as strong as ever.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rottentomatoes.com/tv/glee/s04/|title=GLEE: SEASON 4 (2012-2013)|work=Rotten Tomatoes|accessdate=May 26, 2015}}</ref>\n\nOn Metacritic it recieved a score of 73 out of 100 based on 6 reviews, indicating \"generally favorable reviews\".<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.metacritic.com/tv/glee/season-4 |accessdate=May 26, 2015|title=Season 4|work=[[Metacritic]]}}</ref>\n\n===Ratings===\nAs of April 19, 2013, after 19 of 22 episodes in the season, the season had averaged a 3.6/10 rating/share among adults 18-49 and 8.70 million viewers when counting live plus 7 Day (DVR) Ratings.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/1/glee-renewed-by-fox-for-seasons-five-and-six/|title=\u2018Glee\u2019 Renewed by FOX for Seasons Five and Six|author=|date=19 April 2013|website=zap2it.com}}</ref>\n\n====Live + SD Ratings====\n\n{{Television episode ratings\n| hide_dvr      = y\n| hide_dvrv     = y\n| hide_total    = y\n| hide_totalv   = y\n\n| title1   = [[The New Rachel]]\n| date1    = September 13, 2012\n| rs1      = 3.1/8 <ref name=\"glee4x01\"/>\n| viewers1 = 7.41 <ref name=\"glee4x01\"/>\n\n| title2   = [[Britney 2.0]]\n| date2    = September 20, 2012\n| rs2      = 2.9/8<ref name=\"glee4x02\"/>\n| viewers2 = 7.46<ref name=\"glee4x02\"/>\n\n| title3   = [[Makeover (Glee)|Makeover]]\n| date3    = September 27, 2012\n| rs3      = 2.4/7<ref name=\"glee4x03\"/>\n| viewers3 = 5.79<ref name=\"glee4x03\"/>\n\n| title4   = [[The Break Up (Glee)|The Break Up]]\n| date4    = October 4, 2012\n| rs4      = 2.6/7<ref name=\"glee4x04\"/>\n| viewers4 = 6.07<ref name=\"glee4x04\"/>\n\n| title5   = [[The Role You Were Born to Play]]\n| date5    = November 8, 2012\n| rs5      = 2.4/6<ref name=\"glee4x05\"/>\n| viewers5 = 5.68<ref name=\"glee4x05\"/>\n\n| title6   = [[Glease]]\n| date6    = November 15, 2012\n| rs6      = 2.1/6<ref name=\"glee4x06\"/>\n| viewers6 = 5.22<ref name=\"glee4x06\"/>\n\n| title7   = [[Dynamic Duets]]\n| date7    = November 22, 2012\n| rs7      = 1.5/5<ref name=\"glee4x07\"/>\n| viewers7 = 4.62<ref name=\"gl